### PHASE 4 — APPLY FIXES TO POM.XML

```
Step 4a: Backup
  - cp pom.xml pom.xml.preflight_<timestamp>
  - NEVER overwrite pom.xml.bak (original backup)

Step 4b: Apply KB_HIT fixes first (highest confidence)
  For each KB_HIT vuln:
    - Apply xmlChange directly to pom.xml
    - Append comment: <!-- AUTO_FIX: <artifactId> <fixVersion> KB_HIT -->
    - Log: applied

Step 4c: Apply APPLY_LIST fixes (Ollama decisions, confidence >= 40)
  Sort by confidence DESC — apply highest confidence first
  For each fix in APPLY_LIST:
    - Apply xmlChange to pom.xml at correct placement
    - Append comment: <!-- AUTO_FIX: <artifactId> <fixVersion> OLLAMA confidence:<n> -->
    - Record in attempted_artifacts.txt
    - Append to all_decisions_history.json

Step 4d: Validate XML
  - Run: xmllint --noout pom.xml
  - IF invalid XML → restore from pom.xml.preflight_<timestamp>
  - Log error, abort this iteration, go to Phase 6 error handler

Step 4e: NEVER apply fixes for:
  - Artifacts in user_fixes list (double check here)
  - Artifacts where strategy == "skip"
  - Artifacts where Ollama confidence < 40
```

### PHASE 5 — MAVEN BUILD

```
Step 5a: Run build
  mvn clean install -DskipTests=false 2>&1 | tee logs/build_<iteration>.log

Step 5b: Capture result
  - EXIT_CODE from mvn command
  - If EXIT_CODE == 0 → BUILD_SUCCESS = true
  - If EXIT_CODE != 0 → BUILD_SUCCESS = false

Step 5c: If BUILD_SUCCESS == false
  - Parse build log for COMPILATION ERRORS specifically
  - Extract: error file, line number, error message, class/method
  - Store as BUILD_ERROR_DETAIL (this feeds back into Ollama in next iteration)
  - DO NOT just check "BUILD SUCCESS" string — also check for:
    * [ERROR] COMPILATION ERROR
    * ClassNotFoundException
    * NoSuchMethodError  
    * package does not exist
    * cannot find symbol
  - If any of these exist → BUILD_SUCCESS = false regardless of Maven exit message
  - Log: "Build ACTUALLY failed — Tekton would also fail"

Step 5d: If BUILD_SUCCESS == true
  - Run smoke test if configured
  - Proceed to Phase 6
```

### PHASE 6 — BRANCH / DECISION

```
IF BUILD_SUCCESS == true:
  → Go to PHASE 7 (Push + ADO Watch)

IF BUILD_SUCCESS == false AND ITERATION < MAX_ITERATIONS:
  → Extract build error detail
  → Remove the specific fix that caused the error from pom.xml (restore that artifact only)
  → Mark that artifact's fix as FAILED_FIX in ALL_ATTEMPTS[]
  → Add artifact to collision_state.txt
  → Increment ITERATION
  → Go back to PHASE 3 with build error fed into Ollama context
  → Ollama will now reason with the failure context and suggest adjusted version

IF BUILD_SUCCESS == false AND all CRITICAL/HIGH vulns exhausted:
  → MINIMAL FIX STRATEGY:
    - Keep only the fixes that did NOT cause build failures
    - Restore pom.xml to last known good state (pom.xml.preflight_<n>)
    - Re-apply only the subset of fixes that built successfully
    - Run build again to confirm minimal set builds
    - Log: "Applying minimal fixable set: <list>"
    - Proceed to PHASE 7 with partial fix

IF zero fixes applicable and BUILD_SUCCESS == false:
  → Log: "No auto-fixable vulnerabilities found for this iteration"
  → Write fix_results.json with status: "NO_FIX_APPLICABLE"
  → Exit gracefully — do NOT push broken pom
```

