## CRITICAL RULES (Enforce Always)

```
RULE 1: User-defined fixes are SACRED
  - Never modify, remove, or re-apply user-defined fixes
  - Check user_fixes list at Phase 1d AND Phase 4e (double gate)
  - If unsure whether a fix is user-defined → SKIP it, log warning

RULE 2: Session isolation
  - At start of each repo, ALL in-memory state is cleared
  - The ONLY thing carried across repos is kb.json file on disk
  - Never use ALL_VULNS or APPLY_LIST from a previous repo

RULE 3: Build truth is Tekton truth
  - Local Maven "BUILD SUCCESS" is not enough
  - Always scan the log for COMPILATION ERROR, ClassNotFoundException,
    NoSuchMethodError, package does not exist, cannot find symbol
  - If ANY of these appear → BUILD_SUCCESS = false

RULE 4: Never push broken pom
  - Only push if BUILD_SUCCESS == true (real build, not Maven exit code lie)
  - If minimal fix strategy → confirm minimal set builds before pushing

RULE 5: Ollama temperature must be 0.1
  - Higher temperature = inconsistent JSON = broken fixes
  - Always use temperature: 0.1 for fix decisions

RULE 6: XML must be valid before commit
  - Always run xmllint --noout pom.xml before git add
  - Malformed XML will break all downstream builds

RULE 7: ACS recommendation is a strong hint, not a command
  - If ACS says "upgrade to 2.1.0" but that version breaks build → Ollama finds closest safe version
  - Log: "ACS recommended 2.1.0 — used 2.1.3 instead due to <reason>"

RULE 8: KB hit does not bypass build verification
  - Even KB_HIT fixes must pass Maven build
  - If KB_HIT fix causes build failure → mark kb entry as tektonValidated=false
  - Investigate before next use
```

